column5: Do any of the new "power" type baits contain any fish parts or anything that would make them to be considered organic?  Thanks Dan
i dont think they contain anything organic like fish parts etc but they are biodegradable (capable of decaying through the action of living organisms) but like i said probably nothing organic there
The ANIMAL feathers fly fishermen use are alot more "organic" in my books than the scent on a rubber worm.
